research.implementation_specifics:
DURATIONS (this repo's existing tokens are already in the premium band — match them):
- Reveal fade+rise: 500-720ms (repo: ScrollReveal 500ms, kit `.reveal` 720ms). Sweet spot for hero/section reveals ~600ms; micro-interactions/hover 180-280ms (repo `--dur-fast` ~150-220ms).
- Stagger step between children: 60-120ms (use ~80ms). Cap total cascade ~400-500ms so the last child isn't annoyingly late.

EASING (cite real values, all present in repo):
- Decelerate/reveal: `cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1)` (easeOutQuint-ish, slight settle) — the repo's reveal curve. Also good: `cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)` (easeOutExpo, very premium).
- Snappy UI/hover: the repo's `--ease-snap`. 
- Spring (Motion): `{ type: 'spring', stiffness: 200, damping: 26 }` for a gentle settle; GSAP equivalent ~`ease: 'power3.out'`.

DISTANCES: translateY 12-40px (repo uses both); scale-in 0.96→1; never animate width/height/top/left.

VIEWPORT TRIGGER:
- IntersectionObserver: `rootMargin: '-10%'` (repo) or `'0px 0px -15% 0px'` to fire when ~15% up from bottom edge; `threshold: 0` for reveals, higher only if you need "mostly visible".
- CSS view(): `animation-range: entry 0% cover 30%` (start as element's leading edge enters, finish ~30% into coverage). For a scroll progress bar: `animation-timeline: scroll(root block); animation-range: normal`.

CSS scroll-driven keyframe block (drop-in, progressive-enhanced):
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
  @supports (animation-timeline: view()) {
    .reveal-css { animation: reveal linear both; animation-timeline: view(); animation-range: entry 0% cover 30%; }
  }
}
@keyframes reveal { from { opacity:0; transform:translateY(24px) } to { opacity:1; transform:none } }
```
CRITICAL: the element's DEFAULT state must be VISIBLE (opacity:1). Only the @supports block adds the from-hidden keyframe — so non-supporting browsers (Firefox today) and no-JS users see content, never a blank gap.

STAGGER via custom prop (works for IO or CSS approach):
`<li style="--i:2">` → `transition-delay: calc(var(--i) * 80ms)` (IO) or `animation-delay` for CSS.

PERF KNOBS:
- `will-change: transform, opacity` ONLY on elements about to animate; remove after (or scope tightly) — the repo applies it on `.scroll-reveal`/`.reveal`; ideally drop it post-reveal to free the layer. Never put will-change on hundreds of elements.
- `content-visibility: auto` + `contain-intrinsic-size: 0 600px` (MUST set the size or the scrollbar jumps) on long below-the-fold sections → research shows ~10x faster initial layout on 100-section pages. Note: content-visibility:auto interacts with view() timelines (offscreen elements skip layout) — test, and set a realistic intrinsic size.

LIBRARY SIZES (from motion.dev feature-comparison, gzipped): Motion `animate()` mini 2.6kb, full `animate()` 18kb, scroll trigger +0.5kb, spring +1kb, timeline +0.6kb. GSAP core ~23kb gz, ScrollTrigger adds more. Framer-Motion (React) ~32kb.
